Code of Conduct
Purpose
The purpose of this Code of Conduct is to create a welcoming, inclusive, and supportive environment for all participants. We are committed to fostering a community that respects all individuals, regardless of their background or identity.

Scope
This Code of Conduct applies to all participants in our project and community, including contributors, maintainers, and users. It applies to all modes of interaction, both online and offline.

Expected Behavior
Be respectful and considerate towards others.

Communicate openly and listen to differing viewpoints.

Provide constructive feedback and be open to receiving it.

Collaborate in a positive and inclusive manner.

Use welcoming and inclusive language.

Unacceptable Behavior
Harassment, discrimination, or any form of unwelcome conduct.

Personal attacks, insults, or derogatory comments.

Trolling, spamming, or disruptive behavior.

Publishing private information without consent.

Any other behavior that could reasonably be considered inappropriate.

Enforcement
Community leaders and maintainers are responsible for enforcing this Code of Conduct. They have the right to take appropriate action, including warnings, temporary bans, or permanent removal from the community, in response to any violations.

Reporting Guidelines
If you experience or witness unacceptable behavior, please report it to the project maintainers at maintainer-email@example.com. All reports will be handled confidentially and reviewed promptly.

Attribution
This Code of Conduct is adapted from the Contributor Covenant, version 2.0, available at https://www.contributor-covenant.org/version/2/0/code_of_conduct/.
